description:
&lt;p&gt;The Respiratory Investigation Department is seeking a part/full-time Clinical Physiologist (Respiratory) to join our multi-disciplinary team and help deliver a comprehensive respiratory diagnostic service for Buckinghamshire Healthcare NHS Trust.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The department provides a broad range of respiratory physiological measurements including full PFT’s, allergy testing, exercise tests, Cardio-pulmonary exercise test, hypoxic challenge, methacholine challenge and a home oxygen assessment and review service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The holder of this post will be expected to liaise with patients, carers and other healthcare professionals (across primary and secondary care) to provide and improve respiratory services. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Continuous professional development is encouraged and you will have opportunities to develop further your skills and knowledge. This will include: &lt;br /&gt;• Support to attend relevant professional courses&lt;br /&gt;• Opportunities to gain additional experience and build on new skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In addition to appropriate experience, the successful candidate must possess a Clinical Physiology degree or equivalent qualification (see person spec.) and be registered with RCCP (or be working towards registration).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For informal enquiries, please contact Chris McGillicuddy, Principle Clinical Physiologist (Respiratory) on 01494 426927&lt;/p&gt;
